</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Malaysian government has made further moves against an Islamic sect it
accuses of trying to destabilise the country. According to government edicts
published at the weekend, anyone actively involved with Al Arqam, a sect
which claims 100,000 followers in Malaysia and many more in surrounding
countries, is liable to arrest, flogging and imprisonment. Earlier this
