orthodoxy, said Al Arqam teachings were deviationist. More than 30 of the
sect's followers were arrested over the weekend. Malaysian non-government
organisations and the country's bar council have expressed concern that the
government's moves violate human rights. Brokers said that a drop of more
than 2 per cent on the Kuala Lumpur stock market on Friday was due to
general nervousness about the government's actions against Al Arqam. The
market was stable yesterday in lacklustre trading.
