FT  29 AUG 94 / Emerging Markets: News round-up - Hungary
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A committee studying Hungary's new privatisation strategy, in an effort to
streamline and speed up the process, will present its proposal to the
government early next month. The proposal will include the decentralisation
of decision making, allowing managers of smaller companies to arrange their
sale.
The committee, representing members of political parties and independent
experts, will also recommend combining several companies in equity funds,
which would be offered for sale.
