</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA TYSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's Formosa Plastics Corp, a leading manufacturer of petrochemical
products, saw pre-tax profits for the year to June 30 fall 3.9 per cent to
TDollars 2.45bn (Dollars 91m) as a result of a TDollars 348m loss on its US
operations, writes Laura Tyson in Taipei.
