<TEXT>
Hudson's Bay, Canada's biggest retailer, said second-quarter net profit rose
13.9 per cent to CDollars 18.8m (USDollars 13.6m), or 33 cents a share, from
CDollars 16.5m, or 32 cents, a year earlier, with better results from the
main Bay department store chain, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
