12.9 per cent and Zellers up 9.8 per cent. Including special items, final
profit in the latest quarter was CDollars 40.9m or 72 cents a share.
First-half profit before special items was CDollars 22.2m, or 39 cents a
share, against CDollars 12.1m, or 23 cents, on fewer shares outstanding.
Sales were CDollars 2.5bn against CDollars 2.3bn.
The latest period included the former Woodward stores in western Canada.
