<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 94 / International Company News: Nestle lifts water stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Nestle, the world's largest food and beverages group, is raising its
indirect stake in the San Pellegrino mineral water company.
The Swiss group said it had enlarged its stake in Compagnie Financiere du
Haut-Rhin (CFHR), a Luxembourg company which has majority control of San
Pellegrino, to 42 per cent from 28 per cent by buying shares from the
Italian Gardini and Malgara families.
It expected to raise its CFHR stake further to 49 per cent through purchases
from the Mentasti family, which controls it.
Nestle, which has been building its mineral water interests rapidly in the
past few years, also has a direct stake in San Pellegrino, believed to be
about 14 per cent.
</TEXT>
