<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 94 / Company News (This Week): Hint of recovery in construction
sector - Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The interim results season for construction and building materials companies
kicks off in earnest on Wednesday when half-year figures are due from
housebuilder Persimmon and Rugby Group, the cement company. The gloss has
gone off construction sector shares during the past 18 months. But Persimmon
is expected to have increased first-half profits to about Pounds 14m (Pounds
9.7m), while some analysts reckon Rugby will have raised profits from Pounds
30.2m to about Pounds 35m.
