<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 94 / Business Travel: Airport thieves
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pickpockets have become such a menace to air travellers that Amsterdam's
Schiphol airport is hosting a Pan-European conference on how to foil
pickpocket gangs. Airport authorities from Frankfurt, Brussels, and London
are expected to attend.
Jan Pijnenburg, head of Schiphol airport's crime prevention department, said
it is unclear how many gangs are operating at European airports but added
that they cause significant damage. Most gangs comprise four or five members
and typically make off with between Dollars 5,780 and Dollars 11,560) a day.
</TEXT>
