FT  29 AUG 94 / Business Travel: UK trains strain
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British rail services will be severely disrupted this week by the latest in
a series of rolling strikes by signal staff over a disputed pay claim.
British Rail and Railtrack hope to operate about 40 per cent of services.
Travellers are advised to contact their local station for information on
which services will be running.
The strikes have disrupted train services throughout the summer.
