<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 94 / Business Travel: Korean crash fault
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
South Korean police have laid responsibility for the crash of a Korean Air
Lines Airbus earlier this month on the Canadian pilot and South Korean
co-pilot.
A police official on Cheju Island said at the weekend that Barry Woods and
Chung Chan-kyu had been charged with violating aviation laws and causing
accidental injuries.
All 160 people escaped before the plane exploded at Cheju. A Transport
Ministry report said the voice recorder showed Woods and Chung arguing as
they brought the plane down. A final report will be published next month.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
