<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 94 / Business Travel: China's rail plan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
China plans to begin work this year on a Yuan 6bn (Dollars 697m) railroad
linking the commercially growing southern towns of Canton and Zhuhai, a
Chinese-backed Hong Kong newspaper reported on Friday.
Electric trains should cover the 138km route in about an hour. The link,
which is scheduled to open in 1997, is part of a development plan for the
buoyant Pearl River delta, which includes Canton and Zhuhai.
