FT  27 AUG 94 / Finance and the Family: C &amp;G sets up help-line - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Cheltenham and Gloucester building society has bowed to pressure and set
up a telephone help-line, which comes into operation from Tuesday, to help
its customers understand the terms of the Lloyds Bank takeover offer for the
society. Many account holders are unsure whether they qualify for cash
payments under the offer because of a ruling that customers must have been
members of the society for two years to be eligible. The desk can be
contacted on 0345-889900, from 9am to 5pm, Mondays to Fridays, and 9am to
1pm on Saturdays.
